Data Analysis

California<-map_data("state", region = "california")

Fuel<-stations%>%
  filter(STATE == "CA",
         FUEL_TYPE_CODE == "CNG")%>%
  select(LONGITUDE,
         LATITUDE,
         FUEL_TYPE_CODE)
View(Fuel)

Mapping

ggplot()+
  geom_polygon(data = California,
               aes(x = long,
                   y = lat),
               fill = "white",
               color = "black")+
  geom_point(data = Fuel,
             aes(x = LONGITUDE,
                 y = LATITUDE,
                 color = FUEL_TYPE_CODE))+
  geom_dog(data = Fuel,
           aes(x = LONGITUDE,
               y = LATITUDE,
               color = FUEL_TYPE_CODE,
               dog = "pug", size = 1000))+
  coord_fixed()+
  labs(title = "Pug Friendly Fuel Stations in California",
       x = "X-Axis",
       y = "Y-Axis",
       color = "Legend",
       caption = "Caption")+
  theme(plot.title = element_text(hjust = 3.0),
        panel.border = element_rect(fill = NA,
                                    color = "white"))+
  theme_void()+
  theme_dark()+
  theme_minimal()+
  scale_color_manual(values = "black")
